  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '<b>Storage Modes</b>


    <b>Auto-Generated</b> generates a C# file compiled
    directly into your build. This is the recommended mode for the vast majority
    of projects. No external files, no encryption key to manage, and the data is
    as protected as the rest of your code. It is possible to use this mode for DLC,
    but it requires a game update in parallel, as the auto-generated file will be
    recompiled with the new entries.


    <b>StreamingAssets</b> saves the registry
    in an encrypted JSON file accessible in the build files. This mode is intended
    for projects that need to update the registry without recompiling, such as certain
    DLC scenarios independent of a game update. In return, the encryption key is
    stored in a ScriptableObject that can be extracted from the build using third-party
    tools, making it less secure.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
