  m_text: "<b>How to use SceneReference</b>\n\nAdd a <b>SceneReference</b> field
    to your MonoBehaviour, just like any other serialized field. In the Inspector,
    assign your scene directly from the project files \u2014 no need to remember
    names or indexes.\n\n<i>[SerializeField] private SceneReference myScene;</i>\n\nTo
    load the scene, simply pass the SceneReference to <b>SceneManager.LoadScene()</b>.
    The implicit conversion to <b>int</b> automatically resolves the correct build
    index from the registry.\n\n<i>SceneManager.LoadScene(myScene);</i>\n\nYou can
    also access additional scene information directly from the reference:\n- <b>myScene.SceneName</b>
    \u2014 the name of the scene\n- <b>myScene.ScenePath</b> \u2014 the full path
    of the scene asset\n- <b>myScene.BuildIndex</b> \u2014 the build index resolved
    from the registry\n- <b>myScene.Guid</b> \u2014 the unique identifier of the
    scene\n\nIf the scene is renamed or moved, the reference remains valid as long
    as the scene is in the Build Settings, because it is tracked by its <b>GUID</b>
    and not by its name or index."
